2
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.000
Vile Criminal

3
00:00:14.160 --> 00:00:18.670
One Piece One Piece

4
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:19.420
Wano Arc Wano Arc Wano Arc

5
00:00:18.670 --> 00:00:19.420
One Piece

6
00:01:41.870 --> 00:01:44.540
<b>Rasetsu
 Prison

 Flower 
Capital</b>

7
00:02:05.610 --> 00:02:07.770
Daddy!

8
00:02:13.150 --> 00:02:15.570
Daddy!

9
00:02:15.570 --> 00:02:18.260
Daddy!

10
00:02:23.860 --> 00:02:28.800
Smile fruits are more than
just artificial devil fruits?

11
00:02:45.020 --> 00:02:46.980
Lord Yasuie!

12
00:02:53.550 --> 00:02:54.740
Tonoyasu...!

13
00:02:54.740 --> 00:02:57.990
Damn! We're too late!

14
00:03:11.890 --> 00:03:15.340
How did I not recognize him until
he was strung up there?!

15
00:03:15.340 --> 00:03:19.220
I should commit seppuku for my blunder...!

16
00:03:20.820 --> 00:03:22.930
Lord Yasuie!

17
00:03:36.160 --> 00:03:38.610
Tonoyasu!

18
00:03:38.610 --> 00:03:41.400
Lord Yasuie!

19
00:03:41.400 --> 00:03:44.660
He's dead!

20
00:03:46.580 --> 00:03:49.080
Wh-What the hell's this?!

21
00:03:49.080 --> 00:03:52.840
The Ebisu townspeople adored Tonoyasu.

22
00:03:52.840 --> 00:03:55.210
Why are they laughing?!

23
00:04:10.700 --> 00:04:15.360
That bastard Orochi has
a twisted sense of humor...

24
00:04:18.610 --> 00:04:23.200
<b>Prisoner 
Mining 
Camp 

Udon</b>

25
00:04:27.210 --> 00:04:30.330
That's one crazy bunch!

26
00:04:30.890 --> 00:04:34.250
They're laughing at the execution
of their former daimyo!

27
00:04:34.250 --> 00:04:37.970
How vicious, Orochi...

28
00:04:41.130 --> 00:04:46.680
Sir Yasuie... That was alive
until today defies belief...!

29
00:04:46.680 --> 00:04:51.650
So the enemy knew about
the raid we were planning!

30
00:04:51.650 --> 00:04:55.640
That's why you, Sir Yasuie...

31
00:04:55.640 --> 00:04:57.730
put your life on the line...

32
00:04:57.730 --> 00:05:01.530
to keep our plan alive?!

33
00:05:05.550 --> 00:05:08.750
There's gotta be a good reason.

34
00:05:10.630 --> 00:05:12.500
No matter who he was...

35
00:05:13.250 --> 00:05:16.210
no one deserves to be
laughed at when they die.

36
00:05:16.210 --> 00:05:18.800
No one!

37
00:05:18.800 --> 00:05:22.260
That's probably due to smile fruits.

38
00:05:22.890 --> 00:05:27.270
Some of them are in here with us.
All they can do is laugh.

39
00:05:27.350 --> 00:05:31.440
<b>Bakura 
Town 

Kuri</b>

40
00:05:32.410 --> 00:05:35.360
Inuarashi, Kin'emon,

41
00:05:35.360 --> 00:05:38.360
do you know about smile fruits?

42
00:05:39.990 --> 00:05:43.770
I should've told you.

43
00:05:45.730 --> 00:05:48.520
The smiling faces worn by
the Ebisu townspeople...

44
00:05:49.930 --> 00:05:51.680
are just masks.

45
00:05:53.880 --> 00:05:56.540
They're wearing masks they can't remove...

46
00:05:58.170 --> 00:05:59.530
ever!

47
00:06:02.150 --> 00:06:05.920
A few years ago, Kaido and Orochi...

48
00:06:06.770 --> 00:06:10.320
started importing some kind of artificial fruit...

49
00:06:10.320 --> 00:06:14.050
in exchange for the weapons
that are made in this country.

50
00:06:15.460 --> 00:06:16.760
Smile fruits...!

51
00:06:16.760 --> 00:06:22.470
Eat one of those dreadful fruits and earn
the sea's fury and the inability to swim.

52
00:06:22.470 --> 00:06:27.660
In exchange, you gain
an animal's power and ferocity.

53
00:06:28.650 --> 00:06:31.290
Those artificial devil fruits?

54
00:06:31.290 --> 00:06:35.120
We destroyed the factory
that manufactured them.

55
00:06:35.120 --> 00:06:38.400
Indeed... I heard about it from Master Kin...

56
00:06:39.030 --> 00:06:46.290
but the country had already seen more
than its fair share of the fruit imported.

57
00:06:51.750 --> 00:06:58.740
Kaido's aim is to use them to transform
his men into ferocious beasts...

58
00:06:58.740 --> 00:07:02.680
and create the world's most
fearsome pirate crew.

59
00:07:04.380 --> 00:07:09.270
But there is always a catch when
something is too good to be true.

60
00:07:10.830 --> 00:07:16.150
The success rate for achieving the desired
strength enhancement is around 10 percent.

61
00:07:16.570 --> 00:07:22.070
A mere one in ten of those who eat
a smile fruit gains its powers.

62
00:07:29.450 --> 00:07:34.130
The other nine are left with no
improvements and only the consequences.

63
00:07:34.600 --> 00:07:37.090
They naturally lose the ability to swim...

64
00:07:37.090 --> 00:07:41.090
but as a side effect of these flawed drugs...

65
00:07:41.090 --> 00:07:44.760
they can no longer express
any sadness or anger

66
00:07:44.760 --> 00:07:48.270
and become incapable
of anything but laughter.

67
00:07:48.270 --> 00:07:50.130
What?!

68
00:07:50.130 --> 00:07:55.610
I'm pretty sure Caesar's SAD compound
is the active ingredient in those smile fruits!

69
00:07:56.390 --> 00:08:00.200
Who knew it had such harmful side effects?

70
00:08:00.200 --> 00:08:05.200
Kaido couldn't care less
about his crew's safety.

71
00:08:05.200 --> 00:08:09.160
All that matters is having powerful soldiers.

72
00:08:14.430 --> 00:08:20.920
The Beast Pirates have
three categories of fighters.

73
00:08:20.920 --> 00:08:26.200
Those waiting for a chance to eat
a smile fruit and gain beastly powers

74
00:08:26.200 --> 00:08:27.220
are the Waiters!

75
00:08:30.200 --> 00:08:35.360
The strongest ones who hit
the one-in-ten odds to gain bestial powers

76
00:08:35.360 --> 00:08:36.440
are the Gifters!

77
00:08:39.740 --> 00:08:44.260
Those warriors who ate
a defective fruit and can only laugh

78
00:08:44.260 --> 00:08:45.410
are the Pleasures!

79
00:08:48.770 --> 00:08:53.920
What's worse, to mock the unfortunate ones
who missed their chance at power,

80
00:08:53.920 --> 00:08:59.460
they named the artificial fruit after seeing
the negative outcome on those soldiers' faces...

81
00:09:00.100 --> 00:09:02.100
smile fruits!

82
00:09:09.050 --> 00:09:14.830
I thought the name was strange,
even if those devil fruits are artificial, but...

83
00:09:14.830 --> 00:09:16.520
the truth is just horrifying!

84
00:09:16.910 --> 00:09:19.690
The tragedy goes even deeper!

85
00:09:23.930 --> 00:09:29.740
Orochi found the defective smile fruits
with only a bite taken out of them.

86
00:09:30.470 --> 00:09:35.210
Only the adverse side effects
remained in these fruit,

87
00:09:35.210 --> 00:09:38.920
so they were able to make new Pleasures.

88
00:09:39.670 --> 00:09:40.500
He didn't...!

89
00:09:41.040 --> 00:09:44.620
In the town of leftovers
outside the Flower Capital,

90
00:09:44.620 --> 00:09:47.340
those dying of hunger
every day were crying out.

91
00:09:47.340 --> 00:09:50.350
Orochi had grown sick of it all,

92
00:09:50.350 --> 00:09:57.560
so he mixed the failed smile fruits in
with the leftovers from the capital.

93
00:10:02.020 --> 00:10:05.610
Look, apples! And they're still fresh!

94
00:10:05.610 --> 00:10:09.580
There's enough for everyone! What a feast!

95
00:10:19.070 --> 00:10:23.520
It only took a few times until everyone knew...

96
00:10:24.800 --> 00:10:27.590
exactly what the fruit was doing.

97
00:10:27.590 --> 00:10:31.390
But still, these outcast townspeople...

98
00:10:32.360 --> 00:10:34.890
couldn't disobey their hunger pangs!

99
00:10:53.910 --> 00:11:02.270
That is how Ebisu Town came to be a place
where everyone is smiling and cheerful.

100
00:11:02.920 --> 00:11:05.150
At a glance, it looks so delightful,

101
00:11:05.150 --> 00:11:09.130
but it's a tragic town where people
can't even mourn their parents' deaths.

102
00:11:16.670 --> 00:11:18.220
So...

103
00:11:19.950 --> 00:11:25.110
please do not blame those who are laughing.

104
00:11:34.420 --> 00:11:39.140
Amongst all the species,
only humans can laugh!

105
00:11:39.140 --> 00:11:40.040
Yeah!

106
00:11:40.040 --> 00:11:43.490
♪ That's why you just gotta laugh! ♪

107
00:12:01.280 --> 00:12:03.110
Daddy...

108
00:12:04.360 --> 00:12:07.140
Daddy!

109
00:12:14.130 --> 00:12:15.310
This tragedy...

110
00:12:18.390 --> 00:12:22.530
is Shogun Orochi's greatest sin...

111
00:12:23.250 --> 00:12:25.890
He causes the people great misery...

112
00:12:27.130 --> 00:12:29.760
and even forbids them to grieve!

113
00:12:32.790 --> 00:12:34.430
If this place...

114
00:12:34.430 --> 00:12:37.170
is not hell...

115
00:12:37.170 --> 00:12:39.590
then what is?!

116
00:12:39.590 --> 00:12:41.810
Zorojuro!

117
00:12:49.620 --> 00:12:54.570
This death suits you well, Yasuie!

118
00:12:55.090 --> 00:12:59.950
How dare you live so brazenly in my country,

119
00:13:00.730 --> 00:13:03.920
you impertinent hedgehog!

120
00:13:03.920 --> 00:13:07.170
Or should I say, you wretched rat!

121
00:13:12.070 --> 00:13:14.410
That's right, everyone!

122
00:13:14.410 --> 00:13:21.270
Your former beloved daimyo of Hakumai,
Shimotsuki Yasuie, has died!

123
00:13:21.270 --> 00:13:25.860
Send him to the other side
with your howling laughter!

124
00:13:28.860 --> 00:13:33.030
This is Wano! Bright and cheerful Wano!

125
00:13:33.670 --> 00:13:36.740
It's practically heaven!

126
00:13:41.660 --> 00:13:45.430
Laugh! Keep laughing!

127
00:14:01.890 --> 00:14:02.720
Toko?

128
00:14:02.720 --> 00:14:04.110
Toko!

129
00:14:15.780 --> 00:14:18.450
No, Toko! Come back here!

130
00:14:18.840 --> 00:14:20.950
Daddy...

131
00:14:20.950 --> 00:14:22.830
Daddy. Daddy.

132
00:14:22.830 --> 00:14:25.460
Daddy!

133
00:14:42.860 --> 00:14:44.980
Daddy...!

134
00:14:49.080 --> 00:14:52.940
I have some good medicine.

135
00:14:54.440 --> 00:14:57.070
That's the girl from the soba stand!

136
00:14:57.450 --> 00:14:58.490
Otoko!

137
00:14:59.030 --> 00:15:01.800
She must be Tonoyasu's daughter!

138
00:15:02.170 --> 00:15:03.450
What?!

139
00:15:03.920 --> 00:15:06.910
Daddy, come back to me.

140
00:15:06.910 --> 00:15:09.670
This medicine will heal your wounds.

141
00:15:13.700 --> 00:15:18.430
It's called toad oil and it works super well!

142
00:15:19.390 --> 00:15:20.890
You'll be alright now.

143
00:15:26.390 --> 00:15:29.090
I'm so sorry, Otoko!

144
00:15:30.670 --> 00:15:33.270
That medicine won't work!

145
00:15:38.820 --> 00:15:40.030
Hiyori!

146
00:15:40.860 --> 00:15:44.160
Please, Toko! Come back!

147
00:15:45.640 --> 00:15:46.620
Daddy.

148
00:15:57.740 --> 00:16:01.430
There you are, you little brat.

149
00:16:07.430 --> 00:16:10.100
Clear the way!

150
00:16:31.040 --> 00:16:36.420
I see. She's Yasuie's daughter!

151
00:16:36.420 --> 00:16:39.550
No wonder she's so insolent!

152
00:16:39.550 --> 00:16:42.430
If you...! If you...!

153
00:16:42.430 --> 00:16:44.760
If you...

154
00:16:45.430 --> 00:16:48.310
hadn't laughed like an idiot that night...

155
00:16:49.020 --> 00:16:52.680
Komurasaki would not have had to die!

156
00:16:53.440 --> 00:16:55.520
You little shit!

157
00:16:56.380 --> 00:16:57.940
Daddy! Daddy!

158
00:16:57.940 --> 00:17:03.030
Why you two...! Your family
really knows how to piss me off!

159
00:17:08.830 --> 00:17:11.370
Get up, Daddy!

160
00:17:11.370 --> 00:17:13.500
I'll execute you, too!

161
00:17:16.630 --> 00:17:20.880
Die, you little shit!

162
00:17:20.880 --> 00:17:23.620
Otoko, run!

163
00:17:23.620 --> 00:17:26.280
I do not want to lose you as well!

164
00:17:27.100 --> 00:17:31.020
Disappear from my sight!

165
00:18:26.340 --> 00:18:27.590
Th-They're...

166
00:18:28.640 --> 00:18:32.800
Zorojuro the magistrate killer
and Sangoro the soba cook!

167
00:18:41.310 --> 00:18:45.200
Those idiots have gone and done it now...!

168
00:18:45.200 --> 00:18:47.600
This will be trouble.

169
00:18:47.600 --> 00:18:50.170
But we can't really blame them!

170
00:18:50.170 --> 00:18:53.160
Yeah, I'm glad they swooped in to save Otoko.

171
00:18:54.070 --> 00:18:58.360
Damn you for interfering with the execution!

172
00:18:58.360 --> 00:19:02.450
The rat and his pack keep
coming out of the woodwork, huh?!

173
00:19:02.450 --> 00:19:08.750
Yasuie's brat of a daughter
committed a grave crime!

174
00:19:08.750 --> 00:19:15.130
Hey, samurai! You have my permission to kill
anyone who interferes with the execution!

175
00:19:15.840 --> 00:19:17.030
– Yes, my lord!
– Yes, my lord!

176
00:19:24.810 --> 00:19:28.440
Hey, are those guns pointed at us?!

177
00:19:28.440 --> 00:19:29.520
Oh no!

178
00:19:33.320 --> 00:19:35.880
Run, you fools!

179
00:19:35.880 --> 00:19:36.860
Cut them down!

180
00:19:53.090 --> 00:19:55.920
Sorry, but I don't have time for you.

181
00:19:56.630 --> 00:19:58.180
And neither do I!

182
00:19:58.180 --> 00:20:00.800
Then get the hell outta here, Browgoro!

183
00:20:01.370 --> 00:20:02.600
Browgoro?

184
00:20:02.600 --> 00:20:04.350
It's Sangoro!

185
00:20:04.350 --> 00:20:07.100
You get the hell outta here, Mossjuro!

186
00:20:07.100 --> 00:20:09.070
Mossjuro?!

187
00:20:09.070 --> 00:20:11.510
You've got that moss-ball head!

188
00:20:11.510 --> 00:20:12.750
What'd you say?!

189
00:20:12.750 --> 00:20:15.550
Should I slice you up before Orochi does?!

190
00:20:15.550 --> 00:20:19.450
Shut up! Then I'll put my foot
up your ass before Kaido does!

191
00:20:19.450 --> 00:20:21.160
You want some?!

192
00:20:21.770 --> 00:20:23.490
Daddy!

193
00:20:24.290 --> 00:20:27.210
Otoko, you're safe!

194
00:20:27.670 --> 00:20:30.790
Is he Zorojuro's friend?

195
00:20:30.790 --> 00:20:34.300
Roronoa Zoro of the Straw Hat Pirates.

196
00:20:34.300 --> 00:20:35.920
And the other is...

197
00:20:36.460 --> 00:20:38.430
Vinsmoke Sanji...

198
00:20:38.430 --> 00:20:42.150
The Straw Hat Pirates have
gathered in Wano after all.

199
00:20:42.150 --> 00:20:45.800
Even so, I'm surprised by how
brazenly they appeared.

200
00:20:45.800 --> 00:20:46.730
Hey!

201
00:20:46.730 --> 00:20:49.840
Do you have a problem with
how brazen we are?!

202
00:20:49.840 --> 00:20:52.400
Yeah, do you?! Also...

203
00:20:52.990 --> 00:20:56.650
don't ever address me as Vinsmoke! Got it?!

204
00:20:57.380 --> 00:21:00.280
Then let's finish this right here!

205
00:21:05.620 --> 00:21:06.870
Fire!

206
00:21:13.110 --> 00:21:15.290
That damn ronin...

207
00:21:15.290 --> 00:21:16.590
Ready!

208
00:21:21.300 --> 00:21:22.840
Fire!

209
00:21:27.810 --> 00:21:30.140
Just get Otoko out of here already!

210
00:21:30.140 --> 00:21:31.940
No, not yet!

211
00:21:32.930 --> 00:21:34.310
He's mine...!

212
00:21:35.460 --> 00:21:38.280
He's cocky for a rat!

213
00:21:40.110 --> 00:21:42.110
Take care of her!

214
00:21:42.110 --> 00:21:44.120
What?! W-Wait!

215
00:21:45.140 --> 00:21:46.490
He's attacking?!

216
00:21:46.490 --> 00:21:48.490
Charge! Engage him!

217
00:21:48.490 --> 00:21:51.670
That ronin is coming for me!

218
00:21:52.710 --> 00:21:54.710
Run, Browgoro!

219
00:21:57.960 --> 00:22:01.720
Know your place and mind your
manners, you lowly bastard!

220
00:22:03.160 --> 00:22:05.970
It's up to me to cut you down!

221
00:22:05.970 --> 00:22:09.260
Hey, Moss Head!
Don't charge in without backup!

222
00:22:09.260 --> 00:22:10.600
Ready your arms!

223
00:22:11.190 --> 00:22:12.060
Uh-oh!

224
00:22:12.530 --> 00:22:13.640
Fire!

225
00:22:16.010 --> 00:22:17.730
Stop already, you idiot!

226
00:22:17.730 --> 00:22:20.940
What did Tonoyasu die for?!

227
00:22:24.790 --> 00:22:27.120
Whoa, wait a minute, mister!

228
00:22:27.120 --> 00:22:33.160
We live our lives on the cusp of
evens and odds, just as with good and evil.

229
00:22:33.160 --> 00:22:36.230
Let's put an end to this here!

230
00:22:36.230 --> 00:22:37.000
Okay?!

231
00:22:38.380 --> 00:22:42.290
In this country, we call
everyone's smiling face

232
00:22:42.290 --> 00:22:46.010
an "Ebisu grin," mister!

233
00:22:46.010 --> 00:22:49.060
That's why this place is called Ebisu!

234
00:22:49.060 --> 00:22:52.520
We won't let poverty get us down!

235
00:22:53.370 --> 00:22:54.630
Yasu...

236
00:22:58.480 --> 00:23:03.450
Could he be one of the Red Scabbards' men?

237
00:23:03.450 --> 00:23:06.900
Hey! Protect me, samurai!

238
00:23:08.450 --> 00:23:10.990
Seven-Twenty-Pound Phoenix!

239
00:23:23.970 --> 00:23:26.900
Who is that man?!

240
00:23:26.900 --> 00:23:28.550
Boss Kyoshiro...

241
00:23:29.800 --> 00:23:32.730
My lord, you are too careless.

242
00:23:32.730 --> 00:23:36.350
You should not have come to the execution
with such a meager escort.

243
00:23:36.350 --> 00:23:39.020
But... that ronin...

244
00:23:39.540 --> 00:23:42.190
truly intended to kill me.

245
00:23:44.650 --> 00:23:47.610
Hey, Moss Head! What the hell
do you think you're doing?!

246
00:23:47.610 --> 00:23:50.080
Cool your head!

247
00:23:53.040 --> 00:23:53.080
<b>X Drake
Ancient
Saur-Saur Fruit:
Allosaurus</b>

248
00:23:53.080 --> 00:23:53.120
<b>X Drake
Ancient
Saur-Saur Fruit:
Allosaurus</b>

249
00:23:53.120 --> 00:23:53.160
<b>X Drake
Ancient
Saur-Saur Fruit:
Allosaurus</b>

250
00:23:53.160 --> 00:23:53.200
<b>X Drake
Ancient
Saur-Saur Fruit:
Allosaurus</b>

251
00:23:53.200 --> 00:23:53.240
<b>X Drake
Ancient
Saur-Saur Fruit:
Allosaurus</b>

252
00:23:53.240 --> 00:23:55.960
<b>X Drake
Ancient
Saur-Saur Fruit:
Allosaurus</b>

253
00:23:58.830 --> 00:24:01.500
A surprise attack from that monster?!

254
00:24:01.920 --> 00:24:02.590
Take this!

255
00:24:09.840 --> 00:24:11.970
Ready your fire!

256
00:24:15.560 --> 00:24:19.270
Well, well, well... Verily, this scene
will become a bloodbath...

257
00:24:19.270 --> 00:24:23.130
What should we do?
Just stand here and watch?!

258
00:24:23.130 --> 00:24:26.530
There's no point in
staying out of the fight now!

259
00:24:26.950 --> 00:24:31.290
Hold it! That would ruin the whole operation!

260
00:24:31.290 --> 00:24:36.770
And if we get involved, we'll no longer
be welcome in the capital.

261
00:24:36.770 --> 00:24:41.710
Be that as it may, we cannot let them
desecrate Lord Yasuie's body!

262
00:24:41.710 --> 00:24:44.590
We have to carry him away somehow!

263
00:24:45.170 --> 00:24:47.590
That may be true, but...

264
00:24:47.590 --> 00:24:51.760
Let's split up. Where should we rendezvous?

265
00:24:51.760 --> 00:24:53.490
I'll join you in the fight!

266
00:24:53.490 --> 00:24:58.940
No, wait! Now is not the time for anyone
associated with Lord Oden to be seen here!

267
00:24:58.940 --> 00:25:04.320
That's right. You two need
to slip away without getting seen.

268
00:25:04.320 --> 00:25:05.500
But...

269
00:25:05.500 --> 00:25:10.570
We're the ones who started this,
so we'll take care of it ourselves.

270
00:25:12.270 --> 00:25:13.650
We cannot thank you enough.

271
00:25:13.650 --> 00:25:17.540
We must go, Shinobu.
Leave this to Lady Onami.

272
00:25:20.870 --> 00:25:23.130
Take the lord shogun to the castle.

273
00:25:25.460 --> 00:25:27.690
You know what to do! Kill them!

274
00:25:27.690 --> 00:25:31.510
Kill anyone who stands against me!

275
00:25:32.940 --> 00:25:34.260
He's not getting away!

276
00:25:36.300 --> 00:25:37.020
Fire!

277
00:25:37.020 --> 00:25:38.180
Cover me!

278
00:25:38.180 --> 00:25:40.020
Alright!

279
00:25:45.770 --> 00:25:47.110
Bulletproof?!

280
00:25:47.110 --> 00:25:49.490
What's up with that carpenter?!

281
00:25:51.200 --> 00:25:54.450
Strong Right!

282
00:25:57.580 --> 00:25:58.910
Who are they?!

283
00:25:58.910 --> 00:26:01.960
Who the hell are these guys?!

284
00:26:01.960 --> 00:26:03.580
Oh, there he is!

285
00:26:05.090 --> 00:26:07.860
Ah! He took Lord Yasuie!

286
00:26:07.860 --> 00:26:10.300
What in the world is happening?!

287
00:26:10.300 --> 00:26:14.760
Don't worry! I won't let them
desecrate his body!

288
00:26:15.260 --> 00:26:16.480
Oh no!

289
00:26:18.830 --> 00:26:19.560
Is that...?!

290
00:26:20.470 --> 00:26:25.520
Oh, Usohachi! Thanks, you're a lifesaver!

291
00:26:27.650 --> 00:26:30.070
He's atop that ladder! Bring him down!

292
00:26:32.780 --> 00:26:38.030
Hey now, it's just too ironic
if the sniper gets sniped!

293
00:26:38.530 --> 00:26:39.990
Mil Fleurs:

294
00:26:39.990 --> 00:26:42.870
Gigantesco Mano Spank!

295
00:26:46.060 --> 00:26:47.630
Thanks for the help, Orobi!

296
00:26:47.630 --> 00:26:50.900
And another one of them?

297
00:26:50.900 --> 00:26:56.470
That woman... is the geisha from before!
I knew she was a sorceress!

298
00:26:56.470 --> 00:26:59.850
The enemy is formidable! Surround them!

299
00:27:01.810 --> 00:27:02.680
Onami!

300
00:27:02.680 --> 00:27:04.060
Leave them to me!

301
00:27:04.060 --> 00:27:06.480
Thunderbolt Tempo!

302
00:27:10.880 --> 00:27:12.280
Outta my way!

303
00:27:18.860 --> 00:27:20.580
I think not!

304
00:27:21.000 --> 00:27:22.540
In that case...

305
00:27:24.580 --> 00:27:26.500
taste steel!

306
00:27:36.990 --> 00:27:41.010
I am the shogun's dog.

307
00:27:42.640 --> 00:27:45.480
Poêle à Frire: Spectre!

308
00:27:49.900 --> 00:27:52.980
Let's wrap this up and get the hell outta here!

309
00:27:52.980 --> 00:27:54.370
Yeah!

310
00:27:54.370 --> 00:27:56.860
Lethal Atlas Comet!

311
00:27:57.980 --> 00:28:00.910
Mil Fleurs: Gigantesco Mano!

312
00:28:03.040 --> 00:28:05.330
Weapons Left!

313
00:28:07.090 --> 00:28:09.040
Tornado Tempo!

314
00:28:21.680 --> 00:28:24.390
All troops, attack! Charge!

315
00:28:24.390 --> 00:28:27.860
Rebels are rioting in Rasetsu Town!

316
00:28:27.860 --> 00:28:32.020
By order of the shogun,
these criminals are wanted dead or alive!

317
00:28:32.020 --> 00:28:34.200
Kill them if you have to!

318
00:28:34.200 --> 00:28:36.530
Let's go, you guys!

319
00:28:36.530 --> 00:28:38.650
Kick their asses!

320
00:28:38.650 --> 00:28:41.150
Say, Sir Straw Hat...

321
00:28:38.650 --> 00:28:40.530
That's it!

322
00:28:40.530 --> 00:28:41.150
Huh?

323
00:28:41.150 --> 00:28:45.340
Are those your friends up there
on the light-scroll snail projection?

324
00:28:45.340 --> 00:28:48.920
Huh? That's right. I was told
to keep it a secret.

325
00:28:48.920 --> 00:28:51.730
But I don't really care.

326
00:28:53.540 --> 00:28:54.210
Let's go!

327
00:28:54.210 --> 00:28:58.050
Get in there! You got this! Get 'em!

328
00:28:56.050 --> 00:28:58.050
This can't be good.

329
00:28:58.050 --> 00:29:00.350
Zorojuro! Keep it up!

330
00:29:00.350 --> 00:29:02.100
Hey, Straw Hat!

331
00:29:02.100 --> 00:29:05.210
Is that green-haired guy with you?

332
00:29:05.210 --> 00:29:10.370
Isn't that Zorojuro, the vile criminal
who killed a magistrate?

333
00:29:11.770 --> 00:29:16.360
What a riot! Of all people,
he's gunning for Orochi!

334
00:29:18.200 --> 00:29:22.880
What is it, Babanuki?
It's just getting good. Come back later.

335
00:29:22.880 --> 00:29:27.790
But a criminal has just arrived
from the Flower Capital...

336
00:29:27.790 --> 00:29:31.700
From the Flower Capital?
Who could it be at a time like this?

337
00:29:31.700 --> 00:29:34.000
He should arrive momentarily.

338
00:29:34.000 --> 00:29:36.130
Right through that gate.

